
For local setup (runs on local machine)
 brew tap mongodb/brew
 brew install mongodb-community
 brew services start mongodb-community

# To stop MongoDB service
    brew services stop mongodb-community
# To check MongoDB service status
    brew services list
# To connect to MongoDB shell
    mongosh
# To create a database and collection in MongoDB shell
    use myDatabase
    db.createCollection("myCollection")
# To insert a document into the collection
    db.myCollection.insertOne({ name: "John", age: 30, city: "New York" })
# To find documents in the collection
    db.myCollection.find()
# To exit MongoDB shell
    exit

## show dbs - show databases
  It will have
  | Database | Role               | Think As        |
  | -------- | ------------------ | --------------- |
  | `admin`  | Security & control | Control panel   |
  | `config` | Cluster setup      | Settings folder |
  | `local`  | Server info        | Local cache     |

db.getCollectionNames() - show collections in current database
    db.myCollection.find() - show documents in collection
db.getCollectionInfos() - show collection details